f=\left(1+ \dfrac{z_1}{z_2} \right)\left(1+ \dfrac{z_2}{z_3} \right)\cdots\left(1+ \dfrac{z_n}{z_1} \right) = \prod_{k=1}^n \left(1+e^{ia_k} \right)
\bar{f} = \prod_{k=1}^n \left(1+e^{-ia_k} \right) = \dfrac{\displaystyle \prod_{k=1}^n \left(1+e^{ia_k} \right)}{\displaystyle \prod_{k=1}^n e^{ia_k}} = \dfrac{\displaystyle \prod_{k=1}^n \left(1+e^{ia_k} \right)}{\exp\left({i \displaystyle \sum_{k=1}^n a_k} \right)} = \dfrac{f}{e^0} = f
